      <div class="eyebrow">Project Overview</div>
      <h2>A digital humanities project on cultural heritage</h2>
    </div>
    <p>The project investigates how the Mausoleum of Khoja Ahmed Yasawi is represented in Wikidata and how missing cultural and religious knowledge can be added through RDF enrichment.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card blue">
      <h3>Introduction</h3>
      <p>The Mausoleum of Khoja Ahmed Yasawi is a major cultural and religious monument located in Turkistan, Kazakhstan. It is connected with Timurid architecture, Sufism, pilgrimage and cultural memory.</p>
      <p>Our project uses Wikidata, SPARQL and Large Language Models to examine which forms of knowledge are already represented and which aspects remain underrepresented.</p>
    </div>
