<section class="section">
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card gold">
      <h3>Why we chose this topic</h3>
      <p>We chose the Mausoleum of Khoja Ahmed Yasawi because it is one of Kazakhstan's most meaningful cultural heritage monuments. It combines architecture, religion, identity, pilgrimage and memory.</p>
      <p>The topic is suitable for knowledge graph enrichment because Wikidata already contains basic information, but several interpretive and religious aspects are underrepresented.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Main Research Question</h3>
      <p><strong>What cultural, religious, and historical information about the Mausoleum of Khoja Ahmed Yasawi is missing from Wikidata, and how can it be added using Large Language Models?</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:26px">
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Hypothesis</h3>
      <p>Wikidata contains factual information about the mausoleum, such as location, architectural style, UNESCO status and historical metadata, but lacks deeper cultural, religious and symbolic knowledge.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>Objectives</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Explore the Wikidata entity Q46069.</li>
        <li>Identify information already represented in the knowledge graph.</li>
        <li>Verify missing cultural and religious knowledge using SPARQL.</li>
        <li>Use ChatGPT and Gemini to generate RDF triples.</li>
        <li>Select the most relevant triples through human assessment.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

