    <div class="card">
      <h3>Challenges Faced</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Some SPARQL queries returned too much metadata, while others returned no results.</li>
        <li>It was necessary to verify that the gaps were actually missing from Wikidata.</li>
        <li>LLMs sometimes generated broad or speculative information.</li>
        <li>Human validation was needed to select accurate and relevant RDF triples.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card gold">
      <h3>Conclusion</h3>
      <p>Wikidata contains structured factual information about the Mausoleum of Khoja Ahmed Yasawi, including its location, architectural style, UNESCO status and historical metadata.</p>
      <p>However, SPARQL exploration showed that cultural, religious and spiritual aspects are underrepresented. ChatGPT and Gemini helped generate RDF enrichment proposals, while human assessment was necessary to select the final triples.</p>
      <p>The project demonstrates how Semantic Web technologies and LLMs can complement each other in cultural heritage knowledge engineering.</p>
